subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
A wide variety of forest habitats including cedar (
Cedrus
), fir (
Abies
), and deciduous and evergreen oak (
Quercus
); also thermophilous scrub and steep rocky escarpments and cliffs. The Barbary Macaque is the only non-human primate found north of the Sahara in Morocco and Algeria, with a Mediterranean climate that suffers seasonal extremes of temperature in mountainous areas.
